    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Fabric predecessor to needle lace originating during the 15th century. The mesh ground was formed by drawing warps and wefts from fabric at regular intervals, or by cutting out areas of embroidered fabric and introducing stitching to the void.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
